> > > This is per how the meter is supposed to be used. The van won't start
> > > with the meter installed in
> >
> > hmmm, mine has clips that go on the battery for power.  So both + & - are
> > hooked to battery.  then a third wire is clipped to the battery, but I am
> > trying to remember, thought it was + side of coil but I read the
> > instructions every time I use it to remember
> >
> > what brand of dwell meter do you have?
>
> Good point!  There are two different kinds of meter and it makes a
> difference!  My analog has only two wires and hooks to ground and terminal
> 1 (?+?) on the coil but if you have three wires, then the black and red go
> to + and - on the battery (or other 12V source) and the sensor wire goes
> to terminal 1.
>
> Jeff,
>
> It is barely  possible that your coil/condensor are so marginal that the
> power take-off from the meter make the difference between starting and
> not starting, but it is very unlikely.  If the bus will start w/o the
> meter hooked up, start it and attach the leads while it is running.  If
> that kills it, then fersure you are hooking the leads up wrong somehow.
